Vendored subset of the ERBench benchmark: "ERBench: A Benchmark and Testsuite for Equation
Discovery Algorithms", Kahlmeyer, Voigt, Habeck & Giesen, arXiv:2606.09276. Source: HuggingFace
dataset EquationDiscovery/Equation_Recovery_Benchmark, revision 95bf15c27de68c3f170ca6140d2e4a811c60344f
(fetched 2026-07-10).

train_permissive.csv = the PERMISSIVE-licensed novel-family rows only (per the upstream README
license table + paper Table): SynEq (5303, MIT, ERBench-author-generated), PHYBench (90, MIT per
the paper table and upstream Eureka-Lab/PHYBench), Densities (33, BSD-3-Clause, SciPy-derived).

NOT vendored here:
- OEIS + Eponymous rows (CC-BY-SA-4.0, OEIS-/Wikipedia-derived): under assets_sa/ behind the
  share-alike firewall, minimized (description column removed — upstream rows embed entire OEIS
  entry texts incl. contributor comments).
- Re-rendering families (Feynman incl. bonus rows, SRDS, Nguyen, Keijzer, Korns, Livermore,
  Vladislavleva, Koza, Pagie): dedup to our existing imports; residual novelties recorded in
  the program doc (AIFeynman bonus set -> future import from the original source; 3 extra Korns).
- Strogatz (14 rows): ODE-derived (out of scope) AND GPL-3.0 (sole copyleft family).

Build input for erbench-syneq / erbench-phybench / erbench-densities (tools/erbench_to_catalogs.py).
ERBench's reference sampler (mixtures, extrapolation split, noise protocol) is an EVALUATION
protocol, recorded as provenance in the catalog conventions; the declarative specs here are the
expression + support boxes.
